timetraSASysMIBModule.name: timetraSASysMIBModule

TmnxPtpTime.name: TmnxPtpTime
TmnxPtpTime.description: Identify usage of PTP derived time.

TmnxSysOperGrpCreationOrigin.name: TmnxSysOperGrpCreationOrigin
TmnxSysOperGrpCreationOrigin.description: A number used to identify creation origin for the system operational group.

sbiUplinkAPort.name: sbiUplinkAPort
sbiUplinkAPort.description: Primary bof port used for autoconfig. When set to zero 'uplinAport' would be reset

sbiUplinkAMask.name: sbiUplinkAMask
sbiUplinkAMask.description: The value of sbiActiveIpMask specifies the mask length of the subnet associated with the IP address of the primary bof port.

sbiUplinkAVlan.name: sbiUplinkAVlan
sbiUplinkAVlan.description: Vlan tag to be used on uplinkA, if set to -1 packets are sent out without vlan tag

sbiUplinkBPort.name: sbiUplinkBPort
sbiUplinkBPort.description: Secondary bof port used for autoconfig. When set to zero 'uplinBport' would be reset

sbiUplinkBMask.name: sbiUplinkBMask
sbiUplinkBMask.description: The value of sbiActiveIpMask specifies the mask length of the subnet associated with the IP address of the bof uplink B port.

sbiUplinkBVlan.name: sbiUplinkBVlan
sbiUplinkBVlan.description: Vlan tag to be used on uplinkB, if set to -1 packets are sent out without vlan tag

sbiPingAddress.name: sbiPingAddress
sbiPingAddress.description: IP address to be used for ping-test after booting. This is the last step in the auto-init process

sbiUplinkRouteTable.name: sbiUplinkRouteTable
sbiUplinkRouteTable.description: The sbiUplinkRouteTable contains an entry for each static route configured for the given uplink A or B. These static routes are only used during the system bootup

sbiUplinkRouteEntry.name: sbiUplinkRouteEntry
sbiUplinkRouteEntry.description: Each row entry contains information about a static route configured for the inband mangement. Entries in this table can be created and deleted via SNMP SET operations to sbiUplinkRouteRowStatus.

sbiUplinkAorB.name: sbiUplinkAorB
sbiUplinkAorB.description: If set to 1 this route is for the uplinkA, if it is set to 2 it is for uplinkB

sbiUplinkRouteDest.name: sbiUplinkRouteDest
sbiUplinkRouteDest.description: The value of 'sbiUplinkBofRouteDest' specifies the destination IP address of this static route.

sbiUplinkRouteMask.name: sbiUplinkRouteMask
sbiUplinkRouteMask.description: The value of sbiUplinkRouteMask specifies the length of the subnet mask associated with the destination IP address of this static route.

sbiUplinkRouteNextHop.name: sbiUplinkRouteNextHop
sbiUplinkRouteNextHop.description: The value of sbiUplinkRouteNextHop specifies the IP address of the next hop for this static route. This IP address should be in the same subnet as the ethernet port on the active CPM. The value of sbiUplinkRouteNextHop must be set to a valid IP address for the row creation to succeed.

sbiUplinkRouteRowStatus.name: sbiUplinkRouteRowStatus
sbiUplinkRouteRowStatus.description: sbiUplinkRouteRowStatus controls the creation and deletion of rows in the table. To create a row in this table, set the row status to createAndGo(4)'. The value of sbiUplinkRouteNextHop must also be set to a valid IP address for the row creation to succeed. To delete a row in this table, set the row status to delete(6).

sbiEthMgmtDisabled.name: sbiEthMgmtDisabled
sbiEthMgmtDisabled.description: The value of sbiEthMgmtDisabled determines whether or not the out of band ethernet management port is enabled. When set to 'true', out of band ethernet management port is disabled.

sbiEthMgmtActiveIpAddr.name: sbiEthMgmtActiveIpAddr
sbiEthMgmtActiveIpAddr.description: The value of sbiEthMgmtActiveIpAddr specifies the IP address of the out of band ethernet port.

sbiEthMgmtActiveIpMask.name: sbiEthMgmtActiveIpMask
sbiEthMgmtActiveIpMask.description: The value of sbiEthMgmtActiveIpMask specifies the mask length of the subnet associated with the IP address of the out of band ethernet port.

sbiEthMgmtAutoNegotiate.name: sbiEthMgmtAutoNegotiate
sbiEthMgmtAutoNegotiate.description: The value of sbiEthMgmtAutoNegotiate determines whether or not the speed and duplex parameters will be automatically negotiated on the out of band ethernet port.

sbiEthMgmtSpeed.name: sbiEthMgmtSpeed
sbiEthMgmtSpeed.description: The value of sbiEthMgmtSpeed specifies the speed of the out of band ethernet port. This value is ignored if auto-negotiation is enabled.

sbiEthMgmtDuplex.name: sbiEthMgmtDuplex
sbiEthMgmtDuplex.description: The value of sbiEthMgmtDuplex specifies the duplex mode for the out of band ethernet port. This value is ignored if auto-negotiation is enabled.

sbiEthMgmtStaticRouteTable.name: sbiEthMgmtStaticRouteTable
sbiEthMgmtStaticRouteTable.description: The sbiEthMgmtStaticRouteTable contains an entry for each static route configured for the out of band ethernet port. These static routes are only used to route traffic generated by the out of band ethernet port.The table can have upto a maximum of 10 entries.

sbiEthMgmtStaticRouteEntry.name: sbiEthMgmtStaticRouteEntry
sbiEthMgmtStaticRouteEntry.description: Each row entry contains information about a static route configured for the out of band ethernet port. Entries in this table can be created and deleted via SNMP SET operations to sbiEthMgmtStaticRouteRowStatus.

sbiEthMgmtStaticRouteDest.name: sbiEthMgmtStaticRouteDest
sbiEthMgmtStaticRouteDest.description: The value of sbiEthMgmtStaticRouteDest specifies the destination IP address of this static route.

sbiEthMgmtStaticRouteMask.name: sbiEthMgmtStaticRouteMask
sbiEthMgmtStaticRouteMask.description: The value of sbiEthMgmtStaticRouteMask specifies the length of the subnet mask associated with the destination IP address of this static route.

sbiEthMgmtStaticRouteNextHop.name: sbiEthMgmtStaticRouteNextHop
sbiEthMgmtStaticRouteNextHop.description: The value of sbiEthMgmtStaticRouteNextHop specifies the IP address of the next hop for this static route. This IP address should be in the same subnet as the ethernet port on the active CPM. The value of sbiEthMgmtStaticRouteNextHop must be set to a valid IP address for the row creation to succeed.

sbiEthMgmtStaticRouteRowStatus.name: sbiEthMgmtStaticRouteRowStatus
sbiEthMgmtStaticRouteRowStatus.description: sbiEthMgmtStaticRouteRowStatus controls the creation and deletion of rows in the table. To create a row in this table, set the row status to createAndGo(4)'. The value of sbiEthMgmtStaticRouteNextHop must also be set to a valid IP address for the row creation to succeed. To delete a row in this table, set the row status to delete(6).

sbiNoServicePortOne.name: sbiNoServicePortOne
sbiNoServicePortOne.description: The value of sbiNoServicePortOne indicates service traffic on the port identified by this InterfaceIndex is disabled.

sbiNoServicePortTwo.name: sbiNoServicePortTwo
sbiNoServicePortTwo.description: The value of sbiNoServicePortTwo indicates service traffic on the port identified by this InterfaceIndex is disabled.

sbiUplinkAdminMode.name: sbiUplinkAdminMode
sbiUplinkAdminMode.description: sbiUplinkAdminMode when set to access-uplink, bof uplink would be used in l2 mode,the default mode is network

sbiUplinkOperMode.name: sbiUplinkOperMode
sbiUplinkOperMode.description: sbiUplinkOperMode is operational mode of the system. This object is initialized during system bootup based on sbiUplinkAdminMode setting

sbiExpansionCardType.name: sbiExpansionCardType
sbiExpansionCardType.description: sbiExpansionCardType identifies the expansion card type to the system before boot up. The system will not allow for provisioning of a different MDA than the one currently specified in the BOF. Changes to sbiExpansionCardType equires a reboot to take effect

sbiConsoleDisabled.name: sbiConsoleDisabled
sbiConsoleDisabled.description: The value of sbiConsoleDisabled determines whether or not the system console is disabled. When set to 'true' console is disabled.

sbiPassword.name: sbiPassword
sbiPassword.description: sbiPassword is used to enable the user to configure the bof password.

sbiUplinkAAutoNegotiate.name: sbiUplinkAAutoNegotiate
sbiUplinkAAutoNegotiate.description: The value of sbiUplinkAAutoNegotiate determines whether or not the speed and duplex parameters will be automatically negotiated on the uplinkAport. When set to 'true', auto-negotiation is enabled.

sbiUplinkASpeed.name: sbiUplinkASpeed
sbiUplinkASpeed.description: The value of sbiSpeed specifies the speed of the uplinkA port. This value is ignored if auto-negotiation is enabled.

sbiUplinkADuplex.name: sbiUplinkADuplex
sbiUplinkADuplex.description: The value of sbiDuplex specifies the duplex mode for the uplinkA port. This value is ignored if auto-negotiation is enabled.

sbiUplinkBAutoNegotiate.name: sbiUplinkBAutoNegotiate
sbiUplinkBAutoNegotiate.description: The value of sbiUplinkBAutoNegotiate determines whether or not the speed and duplex parameters will be automatically negotiated on the uplinkBport. When set to 'true', auto-negotiation is enabled.

sbiUplinkBSpeed.name: sbiUplinkBSpeed
sbiUplinkBSpeed.description: The value of sbiSpeed specifies the speed of the uplinkB port. This value is ignored if auto-negotiation is enabled.

sbiUplinkBDuplex.name: sbiUplinkBDuplex
sbiUplinkBDuplex.description: The value of sbiDuplex specifies the duplex mode for the uplinkB port. This value is ignored if auto-negotiation is enabled.

tmnxChassisExtnTable.name: tmnxChassisExtnTable
tmnxChassisExtnTable.description: The chassis table has an entry for each chassis in the system. This table extends the tmnxChassisTable for the SAS platform

tmnxChassisExtnEntry.name: tmnxChassisExtnEntry
tmnxChassisExtnEntry.description: An entry in this table would be created for every entry in the tmnxChassisEntry

tmnxChassisUpdateGoldenBootstrapImage.name: tmnxChassisUpdateGoldenBootstrapImage
tmnxChassisUpdateGoldenBootstrapImage.description: Setting this action variable to 'doAction' causes the current golden bootstrap image to be updated with the image at the location specified by tmnxChassisGoldenBootstrapImageSrc. If no location is specified by tmnxChassisGoldenBootstrapImageSrc, cf1:/boot.tim will be saved as the golden bootstrap image.

tmnxChassisGoldenBootstrapImageSrc.name: tmnxChassisGoldenBootstrapImageSrc
tmnxChassisGoldenBootstrapImageSrc.description: The value of tmnxChassisGoldenBootstrapImageSrc specifies the source filepath or file-URL which will be saved as the golden bootstrap image when tmnxChassisUpdateGoldenBootstrapImage is set to 'doAction'. If 'tmnxChassisGoldenBootstrapImage' is set to the empty string, ''H, cf1:/boot.tim will be saved as the golden bootstrap image.

tmnxChassisValidateGoldenBootstrapImage.name: tmnxChassisValidateGoldenBootstrapImage
tmnxChassisValidateGoldenBootstrapImage.description: Setting this action variable to 'doAction' causes the current golden bootstrap image to be validated and upon completion tmnxChassisGoldenBootstrapImageVersion will be populated with its version. If the validation fails tmnxChassisGoldenBootstrapImageVersion will be populated apropriately.

tmnxChassisGoldenBootstrapImageVersion.name: tmnxChassisGoldenBootstrapImageVersion
tmnxChassisGoldenBootstrapImageVersion.description: This object is populated with the version of the golden bootstrap image when validation is completed. If the validation fails, one of the following values is set: 'Invalid Golden Bootstrap Image' - Indicates the image is invalid.

tmnxChassisRebootAutoInit.name: tmnxChassisRebootAutoInit
tmnxChassisRebootAutoInit.description: Setting this action variable to 'doAction', will reset the bof and reboot the system

tmnxChassisLowTempState.name: tmnxChassisLowTempState
tmnxChassisLowTempState.description: The current Low Temperature state of this chassis. stateOk Indicates chassis is above the low temperature threshold. stateLowTemp Indicates chassis is below the low temperature threshold.

tmnxChassisSystemLEDState.name: tmnxChassisSystemLEDState
tmnxChassisSystemLEDState.description: The current state of the System LED in this chassis.

tmnxHwExtnTable.name: tmnxHwExtnTable
tmnxHwExtnTable.description: The tmnxHwTable has an entry for each managed hardware component. This table extends the TmnxHwEntry for the SAS platform

tmnxHwExtnEntry.name: tmnxHwExtnEntry
tmnxHwExtnEntry.description: An entry in this table would be created for every entry in the tmnxChassisEntry

tmnxHwLowTempThreshold.name: tmnxHwLowTempThreshold
tmnxHwLowTempThreshold.description: The low temperature threshold for this hardware component in degrees celsius. When the value of tmnxHwTemperature lowers below tmnxHwLowTempThreshold, a 'temperature too low' event will be generated.

tmnxFabricPolicyTable.name: tmnxFabricPolicyTable
tmnxFabricPolicyTable.description: This table provides the context to configure the fabric policy in use by different applications. Currently, PBB is the only application using it and only one default object is supported

tmnxFabricPolicyIndex.name: tmnxFabricPolicyIndex
tmnxFabricPolicyIndex.description: the policy ID is the index to this table.

tmnxFabricPolicyCIR.name: tmnxFabricPolicyCIR
tmnxFabricPolicyCIR.description: The CIR specified by the user.

tmnxFabricPolicyPIR.name: tmnxFabricPolicyPIR
tmnxFabricPolicyPIR.description: The PIR specified by the user.

tmnxFabricPolicyCBS.name: tmnxFabricPolicyCBS
tmnxFabricPolicyCBS.description: The amount of reserved buffer space (in kilo bytes).

tmnxFabricPolicyMBS.name: tmnxFabricPolicyMBS
tmnxFabricPolicyMBS.description: The maximum amount of buffer space (in kilo bytes) allowed

tmnxChassisPowerSupplyExtnTable.name: tmnxChassisPowerSupplyExtnTable
tmnxChassisPowerSupplyExtnTable.description: This table extends the Power Supply Information defined in tmnxChassisPowerSupplyTable

tmnxChassisPowerSupplyExtnEntry.name: tmnxChassisPowerSupplyExtnEntry
tmnxChassisPowerSupplyExtnEntry.description: Contains information regarding a power supply tray.

tmnxChassisPowerSupplyAssignedDCType.name: tmnxChassisPowerSupplyAssignedDCType
tmnxChassisPowerSupplyAssignedDCType.description: tmnxChassisPowerSupplyAssignedDCType when set to `m48-dc`, the power supply is -48V DC, when set to P24-dc it is +24V DC. tmnxChassisPowerSupplyAssignedDCType is set to m48-dc or p24-dc if tmnxChassisPowerSupplyAssignedType is of type `dc`, If tmnxChassisPowerSupplyAssignedType is not `dc` tmnxChassisPowerSupplyAssignedDCType will be set to not-applicable.

tmnxChassisFanExtnTable.name: tmnxChassisFanExtnTable
tmnxChassisFanExtnTable.description: This table extends the system fan information

tmnxChassisFanCfgMode.name: tmnxChassisFanCfgMode
tmnxChassisFanCfgMode.description: tmnxChassisFanCfgMode is the configuration object used to determine how the fan in controlled. It can be either user controlled (on|off) or in 'auto' mode where the operation will be based on threshold values.

tmnxChassisFanOperMode.name: tmnxChassisFanOperMode
tmnxChassisFanOperMode.description: tmnxChassisFanOperMode is a read only object which will determine the current mode of operation.

tmnxCardExtnTable.name: tmnxCardExtnTable
tmnxCardExtnTable.description: The tmnxCardExtnTable has an entry for each one of the entry in tmnxCardTable

tmnxCardSysResPlcyId.name: tmnxCardSysResPlcyId
tmnxCardSysResPlcyId.description: system resource policy id attached to this card

tmnxCpmCardExtnTable.name: tmnxCpmCardExtnTable
tmnxCpmCardExtnTable.description: The tmnxCpmCardExtnTable has an entry for each CPM card or module in each chassis in the TMNX system.

tmnxCpmCardExtnEntry.name: tmnxCpmCardExtnEntry
tmnxCpmCardExtnEntry.description: Each row entry represents a CPM card or module in a chassis in the system. Entries cannot be created and deleted via SNMP SET operations. When a tmnxChassisEntry is created, a tmnxCpmCardExtnEntry is created for each CPM card or module in that chassis. Before a tmnxChassisEntry can be deleted, each tmnxCpmCardEntry for that chassis must be in the proper state for removal.

tmnxCpmCardBootImageSource.name: tmnxCpmCardBootImageSource
tmnxCpmCardBootImageSource.description: tmnxCpmCardBootImageSource indicates the compact flash slot where the Boot image file was found when the system last rebooted. For example, if the BOF file was found on compact flash slot 1, the value of this variable will be 'cf1:'

sysLoopbackNoServPort.name: sysLoopbackNoServPort
sysLoopbackNoServPort.description: Second loopback port used for internal sap creation

sysG8032FastFloodEnable.name: sysG8032FastFloodEnable
sysG8032FastFloodEnable.description: Enable disable G.8032 fast flood enable

sysResIngTcamSapIngAcl.name: sysResIngTcamSapIngAcl
sysResIngTcamSapIngAcl.description: sysResIngTcamSapIngAcl sets the resource to be used for Sap Ingress Acl application

sysResIngTcamIngAclMac.name: sysResIngTcamIngAclMac
sysResIngTcamIngAclMac.description: sysResIngTcamIngAclMac sets the resource to be used for mac match from the allocated sysResIngTcamSapIngAcl

sysResIngTcamIngAclIpv4.name: sysResIngTcamIngAclIpv4
sysResIngTcamIngAclIpv4.description: sysResIngTcamIngAclIpv4 sets the resource to be used for ipv4 match from the allocated sysResIngTcamSapIngAcl

sysResIngTcamIngAcl64bitIpv4Ipv6.name: sysResIngTcamIngAcl64bitIpv4Ipv6
sysResIngTcamIngAcl64bitIpv4Ipv6.description: sysResIngTcamIngAcl64bitIpv4 sets the resource to be used for ipv6 64 bit match from the allocated sysResIngTcamSapIngAcl

sysResIngTcamIngAcl128bitIpv4Ipv6.name: sysResIngTcamIngAcl128bitIpv4Ipv6
sysResIngTcamIngAcl128bitIpv4Ipv6.description: sysResIngTcamIngAcl128bitIpv4Ipv6 sets the resource to be used for ipv6 128 bit match from the allocated sysResIngTcamSapIngAcl

sysResIngTcamIngAcl64bitIpv6Only.name: sysResIngTcamIngAcl64bitIpv6Only
sysResIngTcamIngAcl64bitIpv6Only.description: sysResIngTcamIngAcl64bitIpv6Only sets the resource to be used for Ipv6 64 bit match only from the allocated sysResIngTcamSapIngAcl

sysResIngSapIngClass.name: sysResIngSapIngClass
sysResIngSapIngClass.description: sysResIngSapIngClass sets the resource to be used for Sap Ingress classification

sysResIngSapIngClassMac.name: sysResIngSapIngClassMac
sysResIngSapIngClassMac.description: sysResIngSapIngClassMac sets the resource to be used for mac match from the allocated sysResIngSapIngClass

sysResIngSapIngClassIpv4.name: sysResIngSapIngClassIpv4
sysResIngSapIngClassIpv4.description: sysResIngSapIngClassIpv4 sets the resource to be used for ipv4 match from the allocated sysResIngSapIngClass

sysResIngSapIngClassIpv4Ipv6.name: sysResIngSapIngClassIpv4Ipv6
sysResIngSapIngClassIpv4Ipv6.description: sysResIngSapIngClassIpv4Ipv4Ipv6 sets the resource to be used for ipv4, ipv6 match from the allocated sysResIngSapIngClass

sysResFabricPathBandwidth.name: sysResFabricPathBandwidth
sysResFabricPathBandwidth.description: This object is used to configure the system fabric path bandwidth

sysResMaxIPv6Routes.name: sysResMaxIPv6Routes
sysResMaxIPv6Routes.description: Specifies the number of routes to be reserved for use by IPv6. If the value is -1, then there is no limit.

sysResIngTcamEthCfm.name: sysResIngTcamEthCfm
sysResIngTcamEthCfm.description: sysResIngTcamEthCfm sets the resource to be used for Eth Cfm application

sysResIngTcamEthCfmUpMep.name: sysResIngTcamEthCfmUpMep
sysResIngTcamEthCfmUpMep.description: sysResIngTcamEthCfmUpMep sets the resource to be used for Up MEP from the allocated sysResIngTcamEthCfm

sysG8032FastFloodEnableOperVal.name: sysG8032FastFloodEnableOperVal
sysG8032FastFloodEnableOperVal.description: Shows current active value of sysG8032FastFloodEnable

sysResEgrTcamSapEgrAcl.name: sysResEgrTcamSapEgrAcl
sysResEgrTcamSapEgrAcl.description: sysResEgrTcamSapEgrAcl sets the resource to be used for Sap Egress Acl application

sysResEgrTcamEgrAclMac.name: sysResEgrTcamEgrAclMac
sysResEgrTcamEgrAclMac.description: sysResEgrTcamEgrAclMac sets the resource to be used for mac match from the allocated sysResEgrTcamSapEgrAcl

sysResEgrTcamEgrAclIpv4.name: sysResEgrTcamEgrAclIpv4
sysResEgrTcamEgrAclIpv4.description: sysResEgrTcamEgrAclIpv4 sets the resource to be used for ipv4 match from the allocated sysResEgrTcamSapEgrAcl

sysResEgrTcamEgrAcl64bitIpv4Ipv6.name: sysResEgrTcamEgrAcl64bitIpv4Ipv6
sysResEgrTcamEgrAcl64bitIpv4Ipv6.description: sysResEgrTcamEgrAcl64bitIpv4 sets the resource to be used for ipv6 64 bit match from the allocated sysResEgrTcamSapEgrAcl

sysResEgrTcamEgrAcl128bitIpv4Ipv6.name: sysResEgrTcamEgrAcl128bitIpv4Ipv6
sysResEgrTcamEgrAcl128bitIpv4Ipv6.description: sysResEgrTcamEgrAcl128bitIpv4Ipv6 sets the resource to be used for ipv6 128 bit match from the allocated sysResEgrTcamSapEgrAcl

sysResEgrTcamEgrAcl64bitIpv6Only.name: sysResEgrTcamEgrAcl64bitIpv6Only
sysResEgrTcamEgrAcl64bitIpv6Only.description: sysResEgrTcamEgrAcl64bitIpv6Only sets the resource to be used for Ipv6 64 bit match only from the allocated sysResEgrTcamSapEgrAcl

sysResEgrSapEgrClass.name: sysResEgrSapEgrClass
sysResEgrSapEgrClass.description: sysResEgrSapEgrClass sets the resource to be used for Sap Egress classification

sysResEgrSapEgrClassMac.name: sysResEgrSapEgrClassMac
sysResEgrSapEgrClassMac.description: sysResEgrSapEgrClassMac sets the resource to be used for mac match from the allocated sysResEgrSapEgrClass

sysResEgrSapEgrClassIpv4.name: sysResEgrSapEgrClassIpv4
sysResEgrSapEgrClassIpv4.description: sysResEgrSapEgrClassIpv4 sets the resource to be used for ipv4 match from the allocated sysResEgrSapEgrClass

sysResEgrSapEgrClassIpv4Ipv6.name: sysResEgrSapEgrClassIpv4Ipv6
sysResEgrSapEgrClassIpv4Ipv6.description: sysResEgrSapEgrClassIpv4Ipv4Ipv6 sets the resource to be used for ipv4, ipv6 match from the allocated sysResEgrSapEgrClass

sysResIngTcamSapAggMeter.name: sysResIngTcamSapAggMeter
sysResIngTcamSapAggMeter.description: sysResIngTcamSapAggMeter sets the resource to be used for sap-aggregate-meters

sysResIngTcamSapAggMeterOperVal.name: sysResIngTcamSapAggMeterOperVal
sysResIngTcamSapAggMeterOperVal.description: This object shows the operational value of sysResIngTcamSapAggMeter

sysResQosSapIngQMode.name: sysResQosSapIngQMode
sysResQosSapIngQMode.description: This object allows the user to switch between the current mode and 22Gig mode.

sysResQosSapIngQOperMode.name: sysResQosSapIngQOperMode
sysResQosSapIngQOperMode.description: This object returns the current operational value of sysResQosSapIngQMode

sysResRouterEcmpMaxRoutesDst.name: sysResRouterEcmpMaxRoutesDst
sysResRouterEcmpMaxRoutesDst.description: Specifies the number of routes to be reserved for use by ECMP.

sysDhcpSnoopingEnable.name: sysDhcpSnoopingEnable
sysDhcpSnoopingEnable.description: Enable/disable dhcp snooping on the system. Currently for STU only.

sysResRouterEcmpMaxRoutesDstOperVal.name: sysResRouterEcmpMaxRoutesDstOperVal
sysResRouterEcmpMaxRoutesDstOperVal.description: Specifies the operational value of number of routes to be reserved for use by ECMP.

sysResIpMacMatchEnable.name: sysResIpMacMatchEnable
sysResIpMacMatchEnable.description: Resource allocation for ip mac match enable

sysResIngTcamEthCfmDownMep.name: sysResIngTcamEthCfmDownMep
sysResIngTcamEthCfmDownMep.description: sysResIngTcamEthCfmDownMep sets the resource to be used for Down MEP from the allocated sysResIngTcamEthCfm

sysResQosMbsPool.name: sysResQosMbsPool
sysResQosMbsPool.description: This object allows the user to set buffer allocation at node or port level. 'node' means no change in the buffer allocation and works without any decommission ports. 'port' means buffers will be divided and shared across ports. In absence of decommission, buffers will be equally divided. If decommission entries are present, the division will happen as per decommission logic. Refer to tResDecommTable

sysResRouterMaxIPSubnets.name: sysResRouterMaxIPSubnets
sysResRouterMaxIPSubnets.description: Specifies the number of subnets to be reserved for IP.

sysQosPortSchedModeEnable.name: sysQosPortSchedModeEnable
sysQosPortSchedModeEnable.description: Enable disable qos port scheduler mode

sysResMaxIPv6RoutesOperVal.name: sysResMaxIPv6RoutesOperVal
sysResMaxIPv6RoutesOperVal.description: Specifies the number of routes to be reserved for use by IPv6. If the value is -1, then there is no limit.

tResPlcyTable.name: tResPlcyTable
tResPlcyTable.description: The tResPlcyTable has an entry for each user configured system resource policy.

tResPlcyEntry.name: tResPlcyEntry
tResPlcyEntry.description: An entry in this table would be created for every resource policy creation

tResPlcyIngTcamSapAggMeter.name: tResPlcyIngTcamSapAggMeter

aluExtTmnxChassisEntry.name: aluExtTmnxChassisEntry
aluExtTmnxChassisEntry.description: Each row entry represents a chassis in the system. The agent creates the row for the first chassis in the system, with tmnxChassisIndex = 1, which is auto-discovered by the active CPM card. Additional chassis entries can be created and deleted via SNMP SET operations. Creation requires a SET request containing at least tmnxChassisAdminMode and tmnxChassisRowStatus. Note that the first Alcatel 7x50 series product release does not support multiple chassis, therefore there will not be more than one row entry in this table; attempts to create additional rows in this table will be denied.
